<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/water.css@2/out/dark.css" />
    <!-- Light Theme <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/water.css@2/out/light.css"> -->
    <!-- Auto Detect Theme <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/water.css@2/out/water.css"> -->

    <title>Error - <%= Type %></title>

    <!--
        https://github.com/daemonforge/DayZ-UniveralApi/wiki/EJS-Syntax-Reference

        Passed Varibles
        `TheError` This will contain the error text, for the user, or the system error.
        `Type` The type of error passed, you can use this for more advanced templating.
                - "UserNotFound" - player was not part of the servers discord
                - "RoleRequired" - player was missing the role specificed in the config
                - "Blacklisted" - the player has the blacklisted role specificed in the config
                - "Conflict" - player has already linked this discord to another steam id in your account
                - "AlreadyLinked" - player has already linked this discord the specificed account

                - "System" - System Errors
                - "Database" - Error Connecting to the database
                - "BadURL" - A bad URL
                - "Discord" - An error from the discord call
                - "NotSetup" - the discord intergration settings arn't set up on the API
    -->
</head>
<body>

    <% if (Type == "AlreadyLinked") { %>

        <h1>You have already linked your discord account</h1>

    <% } else if (Type == "Conflict") { %>

        <h1>This discord account is already linked with another Steam Id</h1>

    <% } else if ( Type == "UserNotFound") { %>

        <h1>This discord account is already linked with another Steam Id</h1>

    <% } else if ( Type == "RoleRequired") { %>
    
        <h1>You are required to have a specific role in Discord</h1>

    <% } else { %>

        <h1>Error Invalid Link or Request</h1>
    <code style="display: block; width: 100%; white-space: pre;">
<%= TheError %>
    </code>

    <% } %>
    
</body>
</html>